environments and tumor progression and therapy session in ballroom 6A.

495
00:29:05.832 --> 00:29:08.312
She's a great speaker and has a really, really interesting story.

496
00:29:08.392 --> 00:29:11.022
So go check that out if you're interested.

497
00:29:11.032 --> 00:29:14.692
But today I'm going to be focused on more on the role that middle age plays

498
00:29:15.072 --> 00:29:19.032
in driving this increase in incidence, progression, mortality, and all of

499
00:29:19.092 --> 00:29:21.552
these different factors, particularly within melanoma.

500
00:29:22.952 --> 00:29:25.532
So who cares about aging? It's interesting statement.

501
00:29:25.582 --> 00:29:29.372
A reviewer has actually said this to me before, and if you look at healthy

502
00:29:29.452 --> 00:29:33.252
aged tissues, so no cancer or anything like that, what you tend to see over

503
00:29:33.372 --> 00:29:37.152
time in the lung, in the liver, these really common metastatic sites in healthy

504
00:29:37.252 --> 00:29:41.092
aging is you get dysfunction of a huge amount of different stromal cells.

505
00:29:41.132 --> 00:29:44.472
So fibroblasts change the soluble factors that they secrete with age.

506
00:29:44.852 --> 00:29:47.922
They change the way in which they remodel the extracellular matrix.

507
00:29:48.012 --> 00:29:50.932
We get really dramatic differences in angiogenesis.

508
00:29:50.972 --> 00:29:54.652
And what I'm going to mainly focus on today is this dysfunction in immune

509
00:29:54.732 --> 00:29:58.651
cells with age. And when we look at, and as I said, in a normal

510
00:29:58.772 --> 00:30:02.672
healthy human, these dysfunctional phenotypes that we see in these stromal

511
00:30:02.732 --> 00:30:06.712
cells almost mimic exactly what we see in a very aggressive tumor

512
00:30:06.732 --> 00:30:10.502
microenvironment, be that a primary tumor or even a metastatic tumor as

513
00:30:10.532 --> 00:30:14.272
well. And one of the reasons why this is a particular issue in the field is that I

514
00:30:14.292 --> 00:30:18.042
would say about 90% to 95% of studies are done in

515
00:30:18.072 --> 00:30:21.332
preclinical animal models in these eight to 12-week-old mice.

516
00:30:21.752 --> 00:30:25.592
This is the clinical equivalent of a 20-year-old human for a disease where the

517
00:30:25.632 --> 00:30:29.312
median age of diagnosis is 65. So there's a famous saying, we

518
00:30:29.352 --> 00:30:33.132
could treat and cure cancer in mice, but we can't do it in humans.

519
00:30:33.182 --> 00:30:36.872
And I think one of the reasons why translation is so abysmal is because we're

520
00:30:36.912 --> 00:30:40.212
putting these therapies into these young mice that have a fully intact immune

521
00:30:40.272 --> 00:30:43.812
system, don't really have any of these age-related deficits.

522
00:30:44.172 --> 00:30:47.892
Whereas when we see in the clinic, a lot of these patients are in their 60s to 70s,

523
00:30:47.952 --> 00:30:50.072
and they have that age-related dysfunction.

524
00:30:50.472 --> 00:30:54.092
So that's something that I wanted to really start looking at when we set up the

525
00:30:54.192 --> 00:30:58.032
lab. The other issue is that there's often not very good models to

526
00:30:58.092 --> 00:31:01.712
look at colonization or metastasis across a wide variety of different

527
00:31:01.772 --> 00:31:05.692
organs.Particularly in melanoma, the majority of studies are done in the lung

528
00:31:05.752 --> 00:31:09.492
because there are some syngeneic melanoma cell lines that will disseminate into the

529
00:31:09.532 --> 00:31:13.452
lung, and you can study for metastasis, or you could do a very simple tail vein

530
00:31:13.472 --> 00:31:16.552
injection and the cells will go to the lung as well.

531
00:31:16.612 --> 00:31:20.592
A very understudied site in melanoma is the liver because there aren't great

532
00:31:20.632 --> 00:31:24.392
models of colonization. And one of the reasons why this is important is there are

533
00:31:24.472 --> 00:31:28.352
studies now in the clinic that show if patients have localized liver

534
00:31:28.392 --> 00:31:32.252
metastasis only versus patients that have localized lung metastasis

535
00:31:32.372 --> 00:31:36.232
only, the patients with liver metastasis will actually respond much worse

536
00:31:36.272 --> 00:31:39.672
to immune checkpoint blockade compared to those with lung metastases.

537
00:31:39.752 --> 00:31:43.052
So it's important to look at multiple different organs to really

538
00:31:43.092 --> 00:31:46.792
increase the ability for us to give personalized patient care,

539
00:31:47.132 --> 00:31:48.672
particularly with regards to age.

540
00:31:50.112 --> 00:31:53.372
So I was very fortunate to join Dr. Oshani Wiraratne's lab in

541
00:31:53.512 --> 00:31:57.452
2017, for a six-year postdoc. It was the best six years of my life.

542
00:31:57.912 --> 00:32:01.752
And what we actually did is we would get these syngeneic melanoma

543
00:32:01.812 --> 00:32:05.152
cell lines, these YUM 1.7 cells, so the exact same genetic

544
00:32:05.592 --> 00:32:08.992
model. We would put it into the exact same genetic mouse background, a

545
00:32:09.032 --> 00:32:13.012
C57 Black 6, fully immunocompetent, and the only difference

546
00:32:13.032 --> 00:32:16.432
would be the age of the mouse. So we looked at these eight to 12-week-old mice,

547
00:32:16.552 --> 00:32:20.392
young mice, versus these middle-aged 12 to 16-month-old mice,

548
00:32:20.732 --> 00:32:24.192
because this is the time in which the incidence really starts to dramatically

549
00:32:24.312 --> 00:32:28.092
increase. And what we saw very interestingly is that if you form primary

550
00:32:28.172 --> 00:32:31.892
tumors in these mice, they grow much faster in the young

551
00:32:32.012 --> 00:32:35.282
skin relative to the aged lung. However, if you look at

552
00:32:35.312 --> 00:32:39.002
dissemination and outgrowth via the primary tumor or you do these

553
00:32:39.032 --> 00:32:42.152
colonization assays, you see the exact opposite effect.

554
00:32:42.272 --> 00:32:46.152
Melanoma cells are able to grow much more efficiently in the aged mouse

555
00:32:46.232 --> 00:32:48.212
lung compared to the young mouse lung.

556
00:32:48.292 --> 00:32:52.092
So indeed, organs seem to show this age specificity in how they regulate

557
00:32:52.132 --> 00:32:55.982
melanoma growth. And this is a lot of the studies that we were doing during

558
00:32:56.012 --> 00:32:56.752
my postdoc.

559
00:32:57.572 --> 00:33:01.492
So I'll just quickly show what we found during my postdoc, so I can show

560
00:33:01.532 --> 00:33:04.452
you some of the more unpublished data we've been able to get at Fox Chase in the

561
00:33:04.492 --> 00:33:07.712
liver. But basically what we found is that melanoma cells were able to

562
00:33:07.732 --> 00:33:10.912
disseminate into the lung in young and aged mice.

563
00:33:10.972 --> 00:33:14.962
In the young lung, they would undergo this prolonged period of dormancy driven by

564
00:33:14.992 --> 00:33:18.752
factors inside melanoma cells like WNT5A expression and the

565
00:33:18.832 --> 00:33:22.672
AXL tyrosine kinase receptor. However, in the aged lung, what we

566
00:33:22.712 --> 00:33:26.472
found is that aged lung fibroblasts actually secrete very

567
00:33:26.532 --> 00:33:29.892
different soluble factors compared to young lung fibroblasts.

568
00:33:29.932 --> 00:33:31.932
We were able to show this in human and mice.

569
00:33:31.972 --> 00:33:35.332
And one factor that was upregulated in aged lung

570
00:33:35.412 --> 00:33:39.252
fibroblasts was SFRP1. So SFRP1 was able to

571
00:33:39.352 --> 00:33:42.072
basically inhibit WNT5A and AXL signaling.

572
00:33:42.532 --> 00:33:46.292
It would drive expression of this MerTK receptor and really aggressive

573
00:33:46.432 --> 00:33:50.312
outgrowth and proliferation. And not only was that simply just the stromal

574
00:33:50.372 --> 00:33:54.341
microenvironment inducing really aggressive outgrowth in the aged lung, but then

575
00:33:54.372 --> 00:33:58.112
these reactivated melanoma cells would also secrete other factors that would drive

576
00:33:58.152 --> 00:34:01.552
really aggressive outgrowth. So one factor we found was protein S1.

577
00:34:01.992 --> 00:34:05.692
It was able to act on other dormant melanoma cells in the

578
00:34:05.732 --> 00:34:09.453
lung and induce further reactivation and drive really aggressive outgrowth.

579
00:34:10.772 --> 00:34:13.953
So what we didn't address in this study is any immune changes with age.

580
00:34:14.033 --> 00:34:17.352
Unfortunately, in that particular study, we had to use a fluorophore to track

581
00:34:17.392 --> 00:34:20.243
full-on metastatic dissemination and outgrowth.

582
00:34:20.672 --> 00:34:23.852
So we didn't look at the immune system, and what we've done since we've come to Fox

583
00:34:23.872 --> 00:34:27.743
Chase is we now have these 20 color flow cytometry panels where we can look

584
00:34:27.772 --> 00:34:31.642
at differences in lymphocytes, myeloid cells, and some downstream kind of

585
00:34:31.672 --> 00:34:35.272
signaling as well within these cells. And then we only looked at the lung.

586
00:34:35.332 --> 00:34:38.212
So we wanted to ask the question when we started at Fox Chase, what about the

587
00:34:38.252 --> 00:34:38.493
liver?

588
00:34:39.672 --> 00:34:41.513
So we're very fortunate to recruit Dr.

589
00:34:41.732 --> 00:34:45.712
Kelly Couton, a really amazing postdoc who came from a uveal melanoma lab.

590
00:34:45.772 --> 00:34:49.332
So the majority of uveal melanoma cases do metastasize to the

591
00:34:49.372 --> 00:34:53.082
liver, so she had great experience in the liver microenvironment, but we're doing

592
00:34:53.092 --> 00:34:56.912
cutaneous melanoma. So the way in which we wanted to look at this, unfortunately,

593
00:34:56.973 --> 00:35:00.792
there's just no syngeneic melanoma cell lines that disseminate from the

594
00:35:00.832 --> 00:35:03.192
primary tumor into the liver to study this effect.

595
00:35:03.272 --> 00:35:04.872
We're trying to create some right now.

596
00:35:05.352 --> 00:35:08.772
But in the meantime, what we would do is these invasive surgeries where we open

597
00:35:08.792 --> 00:35:12.732
these mice up, we inject directly into the hepatic portal vein, and the

598
00:35:12.772 --> 00:35:16.432
cells go directly into the liver. So we were able to do this successfully.

599
00:35:16.472 --> 00:35:20.332
You can see we only had to inject 50,000 cells, and after 14 days, we

600
00:35:20.352 --> 00:35:22.981
got really aggressive outgrowth in the liver.

601
00:35:22.992 --> 00:35:25.922
The problem is right before we started doing these studies, we started to look at

602
00:35:25.952 --> 00:35:29.792
the different ages of the mice we were using, and we wanted to avoid doing

603
00:35:29.832 --> 00:35:33.692
these invasive surgeries because, I mean, 12 to 16 months versus these

604
00:35:33.712 --> 00:35:37.512
geriatric 22 to 26-month mice, we thought that they would have very

605
00:35:37.552 --> 00:35:41.472
different variable immune responses, even regardless before the cancer is in

606
00:35:41.512 --> 00:35:43.442
there, and we wanted to avoid doing that.

607
00:35:44.612 --> 00:35:48.342
So we were very fortunate to stumble across this hydrodynamic tail vein injection

608
00:35:48.432 --> 00:35:51.992
method. So a normal tail vein, and you can see we use luciferase vector for

609
00:35:52.032 --> 00:35:55.992
this analysis right here, but all the rest of our experiments are done

610
00:35:56.032 --> 00:35:58.692
without any fluorophore or luciferase agent.

611
00:35:58.732 --> 00:36:02.492
But in a normal tail vein, you're putting a very small amount of liquid containing

612
00:36:02.512 --> 00:36:06.202
melanoma cells into the vein, and at least with melanoma cells,

613
00:36:06.852 --> 00:36:10.552
almost 100% of them go into the lung and start to grow out.

614
00:36:10.612 --> 00:36:13.732
Hydrodynamic tail vein, on the other hand, however, you're getting a very large

615
00:36:13.852 --> 00:36:17.652
volume of liquid with the same number of melanoma cells, and you inject it

616
00:36:17.692 --> 00:36:21.252
rapidly, and what it does is it increases intravascular pressure in the

617
00:36:21.272 --> 00:36:25.192
superior vena cava. It induces cardiac congestion, and then

618
00:36:25.252 --> 00:36:29.152
rather going to the lung, it actually drives blood flow in a retrograde direction

619
00:36:29.192 --> 00:36:33.012
in these mice for about two minutes, and it drives all of these cells into the

620
00:36:33.032 --> 00:36:36.912
hepatic vein. So you can see if we use the exact same number of melanoma

621
00:36:36.992 --> 00:36:40.912
cells and the exact same amount of time as a tail vein, all of these cells are

622
00:36:41.032 --> 00:36:44.942
now going to the liver. So now we had this nice colonization model where we didn't

623
00:36:44.992 --> 00:36:48.652
have to perform these surgeries, so we asked the question: Is there any difference

624
00:36:48.692 --> 00:36:50.762
in outgrowth between young and aged mice?

625
00:36:51.292 --> 00:36:54.992
And lo and behold, what we're able to show is that these young mice weren't able to

626
00:36:55.032 --> 00:36:58.932
grow out very efficiently in terms of their ability to colonize the liver, but we

627
00:36:58.952 --> 00:37:02.372
got significantly increased outgrowth in the aged liver.

628
00:37:02.392 --> 00:37:05.602
We repeated this across three cell lines, and they had different metastatic

629
00:37:05.672 --> 00:37:09.452
variability, but indeed, we saw across all three cell

630
00:37:09.512 --> 00:37:13.412
lines that they were able to grow much more efficiently in the aged mouse

631
00:37:13.532 --> 00:37:17.456
liver.So hopefully what I've just been able to show so far is that the lung and the

632
00:37:17.496 --> 00:37:21.276
liver in young mice basically suppresses the ability to grow out, whereas in the

633
00:37:21.376 --> 00:37:25.356
aged mice, they have much higher metastatic propensity, and the

634
00:37:25.376 --> 00:37:28.916
ability to colonize as well. So the next question we had is, what are the actual

635
00:37:28.996 --> 00:37:30.956
immune changes that are occurring with age?

636
00:37:31.436 --> 00:37:33.676
So we had two specific aims we wanted to accomplish.

637
00:37:33.716 --> 00:37:37.576
The first was to look at the pre-metastatic healthy lung and liver to

638
00:37:37.636 --> 00:37:41.576
see if with age, they're actually creating this niche that once the melanoma cells

639
00:37:41.596 --> 00:37:45.256
can get in there, they're able to grow out without being affected by effector T

640
00:37:45.356 --> 00:37:47.546
cells, NK cells, and these other lymphocytes.

641
00:37:47.906 --> 00:37:51.506
And then the second was to look at whether these changes actually also occur in the

642
00:37:51.536 --> 00:37:55.496
post-metastatic niche. So we were specifically looking for consistent

643
00:37:55.536 --> 00:37:59.236
changes in the lung, liver, and also systemically, so either the blood or the

644
00:37:59.336 --> 00:38:02.676
spleen. And we simply started by looking at CD45.

645
00:38:02.706 --> 00:38:06.616
And what was interesting is that in these healthy mice, in the actual peripheral

646
00:38:06.676 --> 00:38:10.016
tissues, we get a significant decrease in CD45

647
00:38:10.056 --> 00:38:14.036
infiltration, but if we look at the spleen or blood, we actually get an increase

648
00:38:14.056 --> 00:38:17.936
in the amount of CD45 cells. So this is kind of not really

649
00:38:17.956 --> 00:38:21.536
surprising to us. I think we see in humans over time, you get this low-grade

650
00:38:21.596 --> 00:38:23.696
increase in persistent chronic inflammation.

651
00:38:23.776 --> 00:38:27.496
But it was quite interesting that in the tissues you actually have less resident

652
00:38:27.876 --> 00:38:31.776
CD45 cells. So the first thing we wanted to find is a more of a

653
00:38:31.796 --> 00:38:35.466
prognostic biomarker, so some of these cytokines, chemokines, and other

654
00:38:35.556 --> 00:38:38.996
factors that may be increased or decreased with age, which might be

655
00:38:39.036 --> 00:38:41.816
effectors of the particular phenotype we were seeing.

656
00:38:41.896 --> 00:38:45.656
So we did a screen, and these were some of the factors that we potentially thought

657
00:38:45.676 --> 00:38:47.836
could have a role in age-induced metastasis.

658
00:38:47.876 --> 00:38:51.756
And the one that stood out to us when we did flow cytometry was arginase

659
00:38:52.036 --> 00:38:55.096
1. Arginase 1 was significantly increased in

660
00:38:55.156 --> 00:38:59.026
CD45 cells in the lung. It was significantly increased

661
00:38:59.056 --> 00:39:02.676
in CD45 cells in the liver. And interestingly, arginine

662
00:39:02.716 --> 00:39:06.456
levels in humans really dramatically decrease with

663
00:39:06.616 --> 00:39:07.296
age as well.

664
00:39:08.336 --> 00:39:12.116
So what is arginase 1? It's an enzyme that breaks down L-arginine to

665
00:39:12.276 --> 00:39:16.256
L-ornithine and urea. And basically, arginine is very critical for T

666
00:39:16.416 --> 00:39:18.616
cell and other innate lymphocyte function.

667
00:39:18.656 --> 00:39:22.486
So when arginine gets broken down, these T cells are no longer

668
00:39:22.556 --> 00:39:25.556
able to proliferate very well. You get a decrease in their

669
00:39:25.696 --> 00:39:29.666
cytotoxicity as well. And a lot of these studies have been done in CD8

670
00:39:29.696 --> 00:39:33.456
T cells in cancers like PDAC. And interestingly, there isn't much

671
00:39:33.556 --> 00:39:37.236
studies done on NK cells, which I'll go into a bit later for our talk.

672
00:39:38.096 --> 00:39:41.816
So in the literature, they've largely been produced by myeloid cells as well.

673
00:39:41.856 --> 00:39:45.626
So we were interested in finding the specific myeloid cell that might be increasing

674
00:39:45.676 --> 00:39:49.406
arginase 1 with age. But before we did that, we went to the human literature first

675
00:39:49.416 --> 00:39:53.236
to see whether or not ARG1 was actually an age-induced factor in melanoma.

676
00:39:53.726 --> 00:39:57.685
So we looked in melanoma patients in the TCGA data set, and we found

677
00:39:57.716 --> 00:40:01.416
that patients with higher levels of ARG1 had decreased

678
00:40:01.436 --> 00:40:05.346
survival. And then we also stratified patients to being under the age of

679
00:40:05.436 --> 00:40:09.196
50 versus over the age of 55, and indeed, ARG1 is increased

680
00:40:09.656 --> 00:40:13.516
in these older patients. So we then wanted to ask the question, what immune

681
00:40:13.536 --> 00:40:15.036
cells is it actually increasing in?

682
00:40:15.116 --> 00:40:18.606
So we looked at these kind of myeloid cells, and we wanted to see whether they were

683
00:40:18.636 --> 00:40:21.796
increased in neutrophils, MDSCs, macrophages.

684
00:40:22.196 --> 00:40:25.436
We looked at every single immune cell, and what was interesting is we couldn't

685
00:40:25.496 --> 00:40:27.656
pinpoint one particular immune cell.

686
00:40:27.696 --> 00:40:31.356
It just seemed to be dramatically increased across all

687
00:40:31.396 --> 00:40:35.136
myeloid cells in the healthy lung and in the healthy liver as well.

688
00:40:35.236 --> 00:40:38.946
So we went ahead with these kind of CD11b positive

689
00:40:39.016 --> 00:40:42.846
myeloid cells. When we look at these metastases, we can see that they're

690
00:40:42.896 --> 00:40:45.676
also significantly increased via flow cytometry.

691
00:40:45.716 --> 00:40:49.676
And when we do these IHC stainings as well on the metastases, we can see that

692
00:40:49.696 --> 00:40:53.486
there's much more ARG1 in the aged lung and liver compared to the young

693
00:40:53.556 --> 00:40:57.476
lung and liver as well. What was also really interesting is we

694
00:40:57.516 --> 00:41:00.896
went back to our previous study, which looked at young versus aged lung

695
00:41:00.916 --> 00:41:04.636
fibroblasts. So these are from healthy human patients, and these are secreted

696
00:41:04.696 --> 00:41:07.556
soluble factors from these healthy human patients.

697
00:41:07.586 --> 00:41:11.276
And previously, we were interested in SFRP1 and factors that drove melanoma

698
00:41:11.316 --> 00:41:14.796
proliferation, but now we went back and looked at some of these cytokines and

699
00:41:14.836 --> 00:41:18.556
chemokines which might change, and lo and behold, ARG1 was actually being

700
00:41:18.656 --> 00:41:21.116
secreted very heavily by aged lung fibroblasts.

701
00:41:21.176 --> 00:41:25.156
So it doesn't just seem to be an immune specific effect with age, but it also seems

702
00:41:25.196 --> 00:41:27.376
to be this fibroblast specific effect as well.

703
00:41:27.976 --> 00:41:31.876
So we went and we got whole lung lysate from young and aged mice, and when we did

704
00:41:31.916 --> 00:41:35.785
Western blots on them, ARG1 was really dramatically increased in the aged

705
00:41:35.856 --> 00:41:37.056
lung of these healthy mice.

706
00:41:38.336 --> 00:41:41.256
So just to recap so far, hopefully what I've been able to show is that the young

707
00:41:41.296 --> 00:41:44.736
lung kind of maintains dormant melanoma or doesn't allow very efficient

708
00:41:44.816 --> 00:41:48.616
colonization, and we have these myeloid cells with age secreting

709
00:41:48.716 --> 00:41:52.476
large amounts of ARG1 along with these aged lung fibroblasts.

710
00:41:52.536 --> 00:41:56.516
So the next question we wanted to ask is, if we flood these young

711
00:41:56.556 --> 00:42:00.516
mice that have low levels of ARG1 with ARG1 using recombinant ARG1

712
00:42:00.536 --> 00:42:04.396
protein, can we actually reactivate melanoma cells

713
00:42:04.436 --> 00:42:08.276
from dormancy in young mice? And then can we actually inhibit ARG1

714
00:42:08.286 --> 00:42:11.466
in aged mice to stop aged-induced colonization?

715
00:42:12.276 --> 00:42:13.836
So we'll start with young mice first.

716
00:42:13.896 --> 00:42:17.346
We basically formed primary tumors with these mice to see whether or not

717
00:42:17.356 --> 00:42:21.296
recombinant ARG1 actually affected them, and interestingly, there was no change in

718
00:42:21.336 --> 00:42:25.316
primary tumor growth. So we then used mCherry to basically look at whether or

719
00:42:25.356 --> 00:42:27.556
not we saw an increase in metastasis.

720
00:42:27.936 --> 00:42:31.496
So this is our PBS treated control, and what we would always see in young mice

721
00:42:31.616 --> 00:42:35.236
after about five weeks is that you could only see these single cell colonies.

722
00:42:35.256 --> 00:42:37.526
So these red cells are the melanoma cells.

723
00:42:37.536 --> 00:42:40.916
But if we treated with recombinant ARG1 throughout that entire primary tumor

724
00:42:40.936 --> 00:42:44.756
process, you can see we're now getting reactivation from dormancy and some

725
00:42:44.816 --> 00:42:47.996
metastatic colonies forming. So that was really interesting to us.

726
00:42:48.356 --> 00:42:52.216
We next moved on to the liver. As I said before, these cells don't disseminate to

727
00:42:52.256 --> 00:42:54.816
the liver, so we had to do hydrodynamic tail vein.

728
00:42:55.186 --> 00:42:58.856
And when we would treat with recombinant ARG1, we saw that there was a significant

729
00:42:58.936 --> 00:43:01.256
increase in colonization in the liver.

730
00:43:02.136 --> 00:43:05.676
So we then wanted to look at what effector immune cells were potentially being

731
00:43:06.036 --> 00:43:09.656
kind of regulated by ARG1. We thought it would be CD8 T cells, but the

732
00:43:09.736 --> 00:43:13.136
main immune cell that we saw getting down-regulated in melanoma

733
00:43:13.636 --> 00:43:17.156
was actually NK cells. So you could see this is our PBS control.

734
00:43:17.176 --> 00:43:20.826
These are a particularly rare subtype, these NK cells, but they do infiltrate quite

735
00:43:20.826 --> 00:43:23.216
dramatically in young mice into the metastases.

736
00:43:23.276 --> 00:43:26.936
But when we treat with recombinant ARG1, we get a really dramatic

737
00:43:27.056 --> 00:43:30.336
decrease in NK cells infiltrating into these tumors

738
00:43:30.416 --> 00:43:34.152
now.So we wanted to ask, does ARG1 directly regulate

739
00:43:34.252 --> 00:43:37.512
NK cells? So to do this, first we did a simple experiment.

740
00:43:37.572 --> 00:43:41.552
We got healthy young mice, we treated them with PBS or

741
00:43:41.592 --> 00:43:44.332
with recombinant ARG1, and just looked at NK cells.

742
00:43:44.372 --> 00:43:48.192
And overall, we saw a significant decrease in NK cells in the

743
00:43:48.252 --> 00:43:51.952
liver and in the spleen. So this seems to be a particular effect that's occurring

744
00:43:52.152 --> 00:43:55.552
even in the absence of melanoma as well when we increase

745
00:43:55.592 --> 00:43:56.212
ARG1.

746
00:43:57.192 --> 00:44:00.952
So we then went back to our aged mice, and we looked at young versus aged healthy

747
00:44:00.992 --> 00:44:04.572
mice. And lo and behold, what we can see is that NK cells significantly

748
00:44:04.612 --> 00:44:08.052
decrease in the lung, in the liver, and in the spleen.

749
00:44:08.172 --> 00:44:12.052
So it seems that even in aged healthy mice, we're getting these decreases.

750
00:44:12.342 --> 00:44:16.332
And when we look at the metastases, we also see that NK cells decrease via flow

751
00:44:16.412 --> 00:44:20.232
cytometry and also via IHC in the metastatic lung

752
00:44:20.292 --> 00:44:21.132
and liver as well.

753
00:44:22.672 --> 00:44:26.252
So we then started to look at some of these cell surface markers that may indicate

754
00:44:26.312 --> 00:44:29.892
exhaustion, activation, inhibition on these NK cells during

755
00:44:29.932 --> 00:44:33.902
metastasis. And what we found is that PD1 and TIGIT expression was significantly

756
00:44:33.972 --> 00:44:37.192
increased. We saw an increase in these inhibitory markers like

757
00:44:37.232 --> 00:44:41.212
KLRG1 and LY49, and we saw a decrease in these activation

758
00:44:41.272 --> 00:44:43.472
receptors as well, like DNAM1.

759
00:44:44.492 --> 00:44:48.092
So with this, we then wanted to test whether or not ex vivo, if we got human

760
00:44:48.212 --> 00:44:52.072
NK cells and we treat it with ARG1, does it actually regulate their

761
00:44:52.112 --> 00:44:56.092
function? So we did this NK92, which is a human NK

762
00:44:56.212 --> 00:44:58.652
cell killing assay with human melanoma cells.

763
00:44:58.682 --> 00:45:01.092
So A2058 are our human melanoma cells.

764
00:45:01.492 --> 00:45:05.082
This is an Acceligen assay, so no NK cells, they grow just fine.

765
00:45:05.432 --> 00:45:08.652
If we add NK in a one-to-one ratio, it limits their growth.

766
00:45:08.972 --> 00:45:12.892
NK cells with a one-to-five ratio significantly decreases it anymore.

767
00:45:13.302 --> 00:45:17.232
And what we were going to do first is treat these NK cells with recombinant

768
00:45:17.252 --> 00:45:20.892
ARG1 prior to killing. So we did three days of NK cell

769
00:45:20.992 --> 00:45:24.092
treatment, but what was really interesting to us is before we even did these cell

770
00:45:24.192 --> 00:45:27.982
killing assays, we actually found that treatment with it significantly

771
00:45:28.052 --> 00:45:31.182
stopped their ability to grow. They basically had the same number that they had

772
00:45:31.192 --> 00:45:33.682
when we first seeded them before the ARG1 treatment.

773
00:45:34.152 --> 00:45:37.232
So we have done sequencing on this, and I'm happy to discuss this afterwards.

774
00:45:37.332 --> 00:45:40.512
I won't have time to show it today. But basically what we did is we got these

775
00:45:40.552 --> 00:45:43.952
cells, we seeded them with the same density as the PBS

776
00:45:43.992 --> 00:45:47.772
control. And what we found is that no NK cells versus our PBS

777
00:45:47.822 --> 00:45:49.932
control, you can see that we get efficient killing.

778
00:45:49.972 --> 00:45:53.852
But if we pre-treated with ARG1, we actually significantly decrease

779
00:45:53.892 --> 00:45:56.472
their ability to kill these melanoma cells.

780
00:45:57.772 --> 00:46:01.592
So the summary with that basically shows that we have these

781
00:46:01.652 --> 00:46:05.362
NK cells that are very high in the lung of young mice and they're

782
00:46:05.432 --> 00:46:09.412
maintaining dormancy. Whereas we have ARG1 being secreted by things like

783
00:46:09.492 --> 00:46:12.792
aged lung fibroblasts and these CD11b cells, which is

784
00:46:12.832 --> 00:46:16.441
inhibiting NK cell number and function and driving really

785
00:46:16.472 --> 00:46:19.672
aggressive outgrowth. So the last question we had is, can we actually

786
00:46:19.712 --> 00:46:22.972
inhibit ARG1 to stop aged-induced metastasis?

787
00:46:23.612 --> 00:46:27.292
So thankfully for us, there is this inhibitor, a CB-1158.

788
00:46:27.652 --> 00:46:30.432
It's a small molecule inhibitor of ARG1 and ARG2.

789
00:46:30.952 --> 00:46:34.772
And it's been shown to be very active in PDAC cancers where

790
00:46:34.832 --> 00:46:38.692
ARG1 expression is quite large. And what we found is that when

791
00:46:38.732 --> 00:46:42.552
we did this in aged mice, we would get these aggressive metastases in our

792
00:46:42.592 --> 00:46:45.592
negative control. But when we treat with the ARG1 inhibitor, we're able to

793
00:46:45.652 --> 00:46:48.632
significantly decrease liver colonization.

794
00:46:48.672 --> 00:46:52.012
So this was very exciting to us. We then wanted to see whether or not it was

795
00:46:52.052 --> 00:46:55.932
affecting NK cells. And when we treat with this inhibitor, we

796
00:46:55.972 --> 00:46:59.492
not only significantly increase NK cells, but we also

797
00:46:59.552 --> 00:47:03.052
decrease PD1 expression on them. We increase some of these

798
00:47:03.132 --> 00:47:06.812
activation markers as well. So the final experiment we did is in young

799
00:47:06.852 --> 00:47:10.792
mice. Given the fact that they have low ARG1 levels and high NK cells, we

800
00:47:10.832 --> 00:47:12.802
wanted to see if it could still be effective.

801
00:47:13.292 --> 00:47:17.092
So we did this experiment, and when we treated these young mice this time, we

802
00:47:17.132 --> 00:47:19.132
didn't see any significant difference.

803
00:47:19.192 --> 00:47:22.902
So this is an age-associated effect, and when we looked at NK cells,

804
00:47:23.032 --> 00:47:26.622
NK cells didn't change, and we didn't see a change in some of these

805
00:47:26.622 --> 00:47:30.312
exhaustion markers. There was a change in DNAM1, which is an activation marker, so

806
00:47:30.352 --> 00:47:34.281
that was quite interesting to us. So in conclusion, hopefully what I've

807
00:47:34.292 --> 00:47:38.122
been able to show is that there is these very age-related effects that

808
00:47:38.172 --> 00:47:41.792
drive different tumor dynamics across multiple tissues.

809
00:47:41.832 --> 00:47:42.242
And that

810
00:47:43.092 --> 00:47:46.501
looking at this ARG1 therapy, for example, we're basically able to

811
00:47:46.572 --> 00:47:50.332
treat these aged lungs and livers, and we're able to see a significant

812
00:47:50.372 --> 00:47:52.182
decrease in their ability to grow out.

813
00:47:52.191 --> 00:47:54.412
But this isn't working in the young lung and liver.

814
00:47:54.542 --> 00:47:57.632
So we really need to look at different aged

815
00:47:58.032 --> 00:48:01.312
environments and different aged metastatic tissues to get proper

816
00:48:01.352 --> 00:48:03.992
personalized therapy to different patients.

817
00:48:05.112 --> 00:48:06.952
So with that, I just want to thank all my collaborators.

